Step 1. Calculate ROE (Return on Equity)
• ROE is defined as the Net Profit divided by the Average Owner’s Equity.
• From the balance sheet:
 – Beginning Owner’s Equity = Paid‑in Capital = 28,000,000.00
 – Ending Owner’s Equity = Total Owner’s Equity = 31,744,117.89
• Average Owner’s Equity = (28,000,000.00 + 31,744,117.89) / 2 = 29,872,058.945
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 3,744,117.89
• ROE = (3,744,117.89 / 29,872,058.945) ≈ 0.1254 or 12.54%

Step 2. Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets.
• From the balance sheet:
 – Total Liabilities (given by Total Current Liabilities) = 8,028,630.43
 – Total Assets = 39,772,748.32
• Debt to Asset Ratio = 8,028,630.43 / 39,772,748.32 ≈ 0.202 or 0.20 when rounded

Step 3. Calculate Gross Profit Margin
• Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue.
• From the income statement:
 – Gross Profit = 8,372,608.70
 – Total Revenue = 28,572,608.70
• Gross Profit Margin = 8,372,608.70 / 28,572,608.70 ≈ 0.2933, which is about 29.33%

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "12.54%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.20",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "29.33%"
  }
}
